examples.en: That's good enough for me.
His qualifications aren't good enough.
He was never good enough to make the team.
Yesterday's solutions are not good enough.
I'm afraid your work is just not good enough.
In my opinion, my work ain't quite good enough.
Would you be good enough to hold the door open?
Would you be good enough to help me with my bags?
The team has enough good players to stop the rot.
It's just not good enough. I've been waiting an hour!
Are your eyes good enough for you to drive without glasses?
They look good enough to trouble most teams in the competition.
He was a good enough player to hold his own against the Americans.
Average grades are not good enough to get you into graduate school.
In your family's eyes, she sniffled, I'm not good enough.
The house was unfit for human habitation (=not good enough to live in).
People ask if the team is good enough. This match will be the acid test.
You're late. It's just not good enough (=not satisfactory or acceptable).
If you can put up a good enough case, the board will provide the finance.
His mother felt he was marrying beneath him (=marrying someone who was not good enough).
One or two songs on the album are interesting, but most fall short of the mark (=are not good enough).
It's just not good enough! *
Your level best is good enough. *
It's plenty good enough as it is. *
You're late every day - it's not good enough. *
Perhaps you think I'm not good enough to meet your bleeding dolled up friends? *
